Reasoning: The paper discusses sentiment analysis of web content, which falls under the sub-field of natural language processing (NLP). The use of machine learning algorithms such as Naive Bayes and K-NN also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CY (Computers and Society), which all have some relevance to the topic of sentiment analysis and machine learning.
